fields.body:
I use django-pipeline and in it's new version it needs a dictionary named PIPLINE in settings.py. python-social-auth seems to pickup this variable as it's own pipeline.  
django-pipeline's PIPLINE looks like this:  
```
PIPELINE = {
    'STYLESHEETS': {
        'base': {  
        ...
```
The error is in social/utils.py line 55, when it tries to split "STYLESHEETS":  
```
def module_member(name):
    mod, member = name.rsplit('.', 1)
    module = import_module(mod)
    return getattr(module, member)
```

