{'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/818/events', 'created_at': '2016-01-12T20:48:33Z', 'closed_at': None, 'labels_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/818/labels{/name}', 'repository_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth', 'labels': [], 'locked': False, 'title': 'Facebook auth should include return_scopes to see which requested permissions have been granted', 'assignee': None, 'html_url': 'https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth/issues/818', 'id': 126272197, 'user': {'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2721922?v=3', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/subscriptions', 'site_admin': False, 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/events{/privacy}', 'type': 'User', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/repos', 'id': 2721922, 'login': 'seawolf42', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/followers', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/seawolf42', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/received_events', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/orgs', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/gists{/gist_id}', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/seawolf42/following{/other_user}', 'gravatar_id': ''}, 'milestone': None, 'comments_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/818/comments', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/818', 'updated_at': '2016-01-12T20:48:33Z', 'number': 818, 'comments': 0, 'state': 'open', 'body': 'When the user approves FB login, they may grant all, some, or none of the scopes requested by the application. By passing `"return_scopes": true` as a parameter to the login URL, the data returned includes a list of scopes that were actually granted by the user.

I am happy to do the work to make this work, but I'm not entirely sure where this should go. It appears to be a parameter on the call to the `AUTHORIZATION_URL`, though when I add it to `SOCIAL_AUTH_FACEBOOK_EXTRA_ARGUMENTS` in settings it is not being picked up.

An alternate way to retrieve this info is calling the Facebook SDK (using facebook-sdk, for instance), but it seems this belongs in the authentication pipeline as that's where I am populating the database with the user's preferences and settings.'}

