fields.body:
Attempting to retrieve the access token when auth_complete is called results in a 401 returned by the reddit servers. The reddit backend creates an invalid header due to byte strings being unsupported with `.format()`. Here's an example of the resulting header:

    {'Authorization': "Basic b'BASE64-AUTH-STRING'"}

The replacement I have working is:

```python

def auth_headers(self):
    return {
        'Authorization': b'Basic ' + base64.urlsafe_b64encode(
            ('{0}:{1}'.format(*self.get_key_and_secret()).encode())
        )
    }
```

