{'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/555/events', 'created_at': '2015-03-19T18:50:06Z', 'closed_at': '2015-03-19T21:52:33Z', 'labels_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/555/labels{/name}', 'repository_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth', 'labels': [], 'locked': False, 'title': 'Make it easier to disable social_details pipeline step', 'assignee': None, 'html_url': 'https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth/issues/555', 'id': 63063903, 'user': {'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/830800?v=3', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/subscriptions', 'site_admin': False, 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/events{/privacy}', 'type': 'User', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/repos', 'id': 830800, 'login': 'johtso', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/followers', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/johtso', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/received_events', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/orgs', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/gists{/gist_id}', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johtso/following{/other_user}', 'gravatar_id': ''}, 'milestone': None, 'comments_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/555/comments', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/555', 'updated_at': '2015-03-19T21:53:20Z', 'number': 555, 'comments': 2, 'state': 'closed', 'body': "Sometimes you don't want to have any user fields automatically populated, and want to handle all of that explicitly, and the obvious way to achieve that is to disable the pipeline step that fills `details` with info from the social account.

The trouble is that currently the second default pipeline step expects a details argument that the previous pipeline step is supposed to supply.

How about feeding in a default empty details argument to the first pipeline step so that every pipeline step can expect it to be there?"}

{'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/553/events', 'created_at': '2015-03-18T12:09:32Z', 'closed_at': '2015-04-04T04:00:34Z', 'labels_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/553/labels{/name}', 'repository_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth', 'labels': [], 'locked': False, 'title': 'get() returned more than one UserSocialAuth -- it returned 2!', 'assignee': None, 'html_url': 'https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth/issues/553', 'id': 62678019, 'user': {'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10459349?v=3', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/subscriptions', 'site_admin': False, 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/events{/privacy}', 'type': 'User', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/repos', 'id': 10459349, 'login': 'CrimsonRay', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/followers', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/CrimsonRay', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/received_events', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/orgs', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/gists{/gist_id}', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/CrimsonRay/following{/other_user}', 'gravatar_id': ''}, 'milestone': None, 'comments_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/553/comments', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/issues/553', 'updated_at': '2015-04-05T08:11:27Z', 'number': 553, 'comments': 3, 'state': 'closed', 'body': " I'm trying to implement Steam login into my project, and I get the error `get() returned more than one UserSocialAuth -- it returned 2!` when I try to do `user.social_auth.get(provider='steam')`. This seems to happen when someone has the same username—the rows in social_auth_usersocialauth are associated to the same auth.User. Attached an image to show what I mean:
![screen shot 2015-03-18 at 8 01 37 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10459349/6708411/f5a54cf0-cdaa-11e4-93f5-dc3774e8809b.png)

As a side note, is it a good idea to store the Steam name as username field in auth.User? Steam names can be changed and are not unique. I think it's better to just return something unique for the username field, like UID."}

