fields.body:
[In social.storage.base there is a property called `tokens`](https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth/blob/master/social/storage/base.py#L36-L39). In django-social-auth this used to return a dictionary containing different token types.

Now it returns the access token:

```python
@property
def tokens(self):
    """Return access_token stored in extra_data or None"""
    return self.extra_data.get('access_token')
```

The pluralized naming doesn't really make sense though. What about deprecating `tokens` and moving the functionality to an `access_token` property?

