python-openid adds two objects (```_yadis_services__openid_consumer_```, ```_openid_consumer_last_token```) that can't be serialized with JSON resulting in an error ```is not JSON serializable``` (a similar issue can be be found [here](https://github.com/openid/python-openid/issues/17)).

This pull request is mainly copy-pasted from [this commit](https://github.com/mitsuhiko/flask-openid/commit/a7993a1f1f4e76e8df801dd436b5ae869a1a4de1) and adds a session wrapper that will take care of pickle.dumps and pickle.loads the two objects so they can be serialized to JSON.", 'pull_request': {'patch_url': 'https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth/pull/16.patch', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth/pull/16', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/omab/python-social-auth/pulls/16', 'diff_url': 'https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth/pull/16.diff'}}

